+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1772759302280,"sessionID":"ses_33f4fd2b5ffeGXtRMMjxvu6ZWZ","part":{"id":"prt_cc0b03dba001moR2QGDU71MJsC","sessionID":"ses_33f4fd2b5ffeGXtRMMjxvu6ZWZ","messageID":"msg_cc0b03bb5002GERpFUBxgPyJsI","type":"tool","callID":"c87c66895","tool":"write","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","content":"---\napplyTo: \"**\"\n---\n\n# Ralph Plan for Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor\n\n## Original Request\nBuild a collaborative real-time document editing server with the following features:\n1. REST API for CRUD operations on documents (title, content) with version history.\n2. WebSocket real-time collaboration using operations (insert/delete) and broadcast to other clients.\n3. Conflict resolution via Operational Transform (OT) or CRDT to ensure convergence.\n4. Persistence using SQLite (`better-sqlite3`) for documents and version history.\n5. Robustness: handle >=10 concurrent clients, reject malformed ops gracefully.\n6. Export a `createApp` factory from `src/server.ts` (or `src/index.ts`) returning `{ app, start(port?), stop() }`.\n7. Use TypeScript, Express, ws, better-sqlite3. All dependencies installed.\n\n## Goal / Success Criteria\n- `npm run build` succeeds.\n- `npm run lint` passes.\n- Server handles full lifecycle: REST create doc, WebSocket connect, send edits, receive broadcasts, verify convergence via REST.\n- Documents persist across restarts.\n- Concurrency correctness with at least 10 clients.\n- Tests pass (we will add basic tests).\n\n## Approach\n### 1. Project Setup\n- Create `src/server.ts` implementing `createApp`.\n- Set up Express app with routes: `POST /documents`, `GET /documents/:id`, `PUT /documents/:id`, `GET /documents`, `DELETE /documents/:id`, `GET /documents/:id/versions`.\n- Use better-sqlite3 to create tables `documents(id INTEGER PK, title TEXT, content TEXT)` and `versions(id INTEGER PK, doc_id INTEGER, title TEXT, content TEXT, timestamp DATETIME)`.\n- On each update, insert a version record.\n\n### 2. WebSocket Layer\n- Use `ws` library. Attach to HTTP server.\n- Path `/ws/documents/:id`.\n- On connection, send current document state `{type: \"sync\", content, version}`.\n- Define operation message format: `{type: \"op\", opId, clientId, version, ops: [{pos:number, insert?:string, delete?:number}]}`.\n- Maintain per-document in-memory state with current content and version number.\n- Broadcast received ops to other clients after transforming against pending ops using OT.\n\n### 3. Operational Transform Implementation\n- Implement a simple OT algorithm for text: transform incoming ops against concurrent ops based on version numbers.\n- Keep a queue of pending ops per document with their version numbers.\n- When a client sends op with base version `v`, transform it against ops `v+1 .. currentVersion` before applying.\n- Increment document version after applying.\n- Send transformed op to all other clients.\n- For simplicity, we will implement a basic character-level OT sufficient for insert/delete.\n\n### 4. Persistence & Recovery\n- On server start, load documents from DB into in-memory map.\n- When ops are applied, update DB content and create version row.\n- On restart, in-memory state rebuilt from DB.\n\n### 5. Robustness\n- Validate ops: positions within bounds, insert string non-empty, delete positive integer.\n- If invalid, send error message `{type: \"error\", message}` and close connection optionally.\n- Limit concurrent connections per doc using a Set.\n\n### 6. Server Lifecycle API\n- `createApp(dbPath?: string)` creates DB (default `:memory:` or `./data.db`).\n- Returns `{ app, start(port?), stop() }` where `start` creates HTTP server, attaches WS, listens on given port (0 for random). Returns actual port.\n- `stop` closes WS server and HTTP server, and DB connection.\n\n### 7. Tests\n- Use Vitest + supertest for REST endpoints.\n- Use `ws` client library in tests to simulate multiple clients editing same doc, verify final content matches expected after concurrent ops.\n- Test persistence by stopping server, restarting, and checking content.\n\n### 8. Linting / Build\n- Ensure TypeScript compiles (`npm run build`). Add any necessary tsconfig tweaks.\n\n## Key Files\n- `src/server.ts` – main server implementation.\n- `src/db.ts` – DB initialization and helper functions.\n- `src/ot.ts` – Operational Transform utilities.\n- `src/types.ts` – Type definitions for messages.\n- `src/__tests__/*.test.ts` – tests.\n\n## Risks & Mitigations\n- **OT correctness**: Implement minimal but correct algorithm; test with concurrent inserts/deletes.\n- **Performance**: For 10 clients, simple in-memory structures suffice.\n- **Version sync**: Ensure version numbers are correctly tracked; include version in messages.\n- **Database locks**: better-sqlite3 is synchronous; acceptable for low load.\n- **Edge cases**: Malformed ops, out-of-bounds positions – validate and reject.\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Create project files (`src/db.ts`, `src/ot.ts`, `src/server.ts`).\n2. Implement DB schema creation.\n3. Implement OT transform functions.\n4. Build Express routes.\n5. Set up WebSocket handling.\n6. Write basic tests.\n7. Run lint/build/tests iteratively.\n","encoding":"utf8"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","title":".opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/workspace/.opencode/plans/ralph-plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"time":{"start":1772759302272,"end":1772759302279}}}}
